    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i know you're supposed to say that, but it feels like a cliche. i've been here for a year and i literally don't know my neighbors' names. if i didn't show up to my remote job for a week, they'd probably just assume my internet was down. there's just no weight to my existence here.",
